text.tspan: pyrrhic (a victory that comes at a cost that's not worth it)
benighted (fallen into a state of ignorance)
tendentious (likely to lean towards a contrevertial view)
Hedge (to limit or qualify a statement; to avoid making a direct statement)
Gerrymander (to manipulate voting districts to favour a particular party)
malapropism (the confusion of a word with another word that sounds similar)
Sangfroid (calmness or poise in difficult situations)
arriviste (a person who has recently reached a position of power; social climber))
protean (readily taking on different roles; versatile)
schadenfreude (joy from watching sufferings of others)
Illustrious (widely known and esteemed; having or conferring glory)
cede (give up possesion or control over)
raconteur (a person skilled in telling anecdotes)
sagacious (having good judgement and acute insight)
impute (attribute responsibility or fault to something)
unforthcoming (uncooperative; not willing to give up information)
effrontery (audacious (or arrogant) behaviour that you've no right to)
duplicity (deceitfulness, pretending to want one thing but interested in something else)
umbrage (feeling of anger caused by being offended)
hagiographic (excessively flattering towards someone's life or work)
anodyne (something that soothes or relieves pain +)
primacy (state of being first in importance)
solecism, gaffe (a socially awkward or tactless act)
evasive (not doing one's duty + abandon building)
